{
  "texts": [
    "Yet the risks deepen in parallel.",
    "Each AI generation has brought ethical, social, and regulatory concerns that must be grappled with, from bias and privacy to job displacement and environmental impact.",
    "AI 4.0, with its prospect of self-directed or conscious systems, amplifies these dilemmas further, underscoring the need for robust AI alignment, interpretability, and governance frameworks.",
    "Ultimately, the future of AI does not hinge on any single algorithmic breakthrough or hardware leap.",
    "Instead, it will depend on how researchers, policymakers, ethicists, and the public collaborate to shape its evolution."
  ]
}